  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Shifting the Power through Developing the Capacity of SOS Sahel Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Along side implementing long term development programs,SOS Sahel Ethiopia has been engaged in humanitarian interventions in partnership with government and International organization.TheAgnecy has implemented various humanitarian programs for disaster-affected smallholder farmesrs and pastoralists in Ahmara,  Oromia and SNNP region since 1994.Humanitarian Interventions of SOS Sahel has been financially supported by EU, DFID, CordAid, Trocair/Cafod, Oxfam Canada , Chrisrtian AID, HelpAgeInternational,USAID. Despite its  good track record in managing humanitarian response programs SOS Sahel has been largely receiving humanitarian response funds through intermediary organizations like International Non- Governmental Organizatyion( INGOs). This is because the organization does not have the required institutional capacity to directly access funds from the international donors organizations. The inability of local organizations to directly access funds from international socurces has undermind the effectiveness of Humanitarian response. Different assessment findings indicated that the current humanitarian response interventions (International NGO-  Local NGO- disaster affected Communities) resulted in lack of efficiency, effectiveness a</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall goal of the project is to enhance Institutional capacity of  SOS Sahel Ethiopia to access Humanitarian Funds directly from international donors.</narrative>
  </description>
